Preamble
--------

Stick‑Gen is an open generative framework for synthesizing expressive,
physics‑aware stick‑figure motion. This Prosocial Public License (PPL‑3%)
is designed to:

  • Enable generous open use by individuals, researchers, and early‑stage
    teams; and

  • Require successful commercial users above a defined revenue threshold
    to share a small portion of value (3%) back to support ongoing R&D on
    Stick‑Gen and related tooling.

By using, copying, modifying, or distributing this software, you accept
this License.

This License is not legal advice. You should consult with your own legal
counsel before relying on it.

1. Definitions
--------------

“Project” means the Stick‑Gen motion generation framework and associated
code and documentation in this repository that Gestura AI designates as
licensed under this Prosocial Public License – PPL‑3% (the “License”).

“You” (or “Your”) means an individual or legal entity exercising
permissions under this License.

“Commercial Use” means use of the Project in or for the provision of
products or services for which You or Your affiliates receive monetary
or other commercial value.

“Attributable Revenue” means the portion of Your annual gross revenue
reasonably attributable to products or services that incorporate or
depend on the Project.

“Qualifying User” means any You whose global annual gross revenue from
all activities exceeds USD $1,000,000 in a given fiscal year and that
engages in Commercial Use of the Project in that year.

“Legacy MIT Versions” means any prior tagged releases or commits of this
repository that Gestura AI has explicitly identified as licensed under
the MIT License.

2. Grant of Rights
------------------

Subject to the conditions in this License, Gestura AI hereby grants You
a worldwide, non‑exclusive, non‑transferable, royalty‑free (except as
set forth in Section 3), irrevocable license to:

  • use, copy, and run the Project;
  • create derivative works of the Project;
  • distribute the Project and derivative works; and
  • host or make available the Project as part of a service,

in source or object form, for any purpose, including Commercial Use.

3. Prosocial Revenue Share (PPL‑3%)
-----------------------------------

3.1 Non‑Qualifying Users (below threshold).
If You are not a Qualifying User, You may exercise all rights granted in
Section 2 without owing any payment under this Section 3, subject to the
other conditions in this License.

3.2 Qualifying Users (above threshold).
If You are a Qualifying User and engage in Commercial Use of the
Project during any fiscal year, You must either:

  (a) Remit to Gestura AI, or to a designated non‑profit or foundation
      controlled by Gestura AI, an amount equal to **3% (three percent)**
      of Attributable Revenue for that year (“PPL‑3% Share”); or

  (b) Obtain a separate written commercial license from Gestura AI that
      supersedes or modifies this obligation.

3.3 Revenue threshold.
For clarity, the PPL‑3% Share applies only if both (i) Your global
annual gross revenue from all activities exceeds USD $1,000,000 in the
relevant fiscal year and (ii) You engage in Commercial Use of the
Project in that year.

4. Funding Mechanisms
---------------------

4.1 Approved mechanisms.
Unless otherwise agreed in writing, the PPL‑3% Share may be satisfied by
making annual payments via one or more of the following mechanisms:

  • GitHub Sponsors or equivalent platforms to Gestura AI
    (for example: https://github.com/sponsors/gestura-ai); or

  • Direct contributions to a non‑profit foundation or fiscal sponsor
    publicly designated by Gestura AI at https://gestura.ai as an
    approved PPL funding recipient; or

  • Any other mechanism expressly approved in writing by Gestura AI.

4.2 Use of funds.
Gestura AI intends (but is not legally obligated) to direct PPL‑3%
funds primarily to research and development related to Stick‑Gen,
including predictive gestures, 2.5D/3D rendering, multimodal
conditioning, voice and agentic interfaces, and safety tooling.

5. Non‑Commercial, Research, and OSS Uses
-----------------------------------------

Academic institutions, non‑profit organizations, individuals, and open‑
source projects that use the Project for non‑commercial research,
education, experimentation, or open‑source development do not owe any
payment under Section 3, regardless of revenue, provided that they
comply with the other terms of this License.

6. Source Availability and Reciprocity
--------------------------------------

If You distribute the Project or derivative works of the Project, You
must:

  • include a copy of this License; and
  • clearly indicate any modifications You have made; and
  • license such modifications to the Project under this same License.

This Section does not require You to open‑source Your entire product,
only the portions of code that are derivative works of the Project.

